Merge pull request #68 from smurching/github-pages

Updates documentation to build with Jekyll so we can host it on Github pages. See https://smurching.github.io/spark-sklearn/ to see what the hosted docs will look like.

Since Github pages [doesn't support the custom Jekyll plugins](https://help.github.com/articles/adding-jekyll-plugins-to-a-github-pages-site/) used to build the docs, docs must be pre-built & pushed. 

This PR contains only the code changes needed to update the docs, while #67 also contains the prebuilt docs (static HTML + CSS + JS)

Summary of changes:
* docs/_plugins/copy_api_dirs.rb: Builds docs. Runs the existing `python/gen-docs.sh` script to generate docs and copies them into the appropriate (jekyll-specific) directory.
* docs/README.md: New doc build instructions
* python/docs/conf.py: Now reads spark-sklearn version from environment variables
* requirements-docs.txt: Requirements file for building docs.

To build the docs:
* Install Python & Ruby dependencies as specified in `docs/README.md`
* Run `jekyll build` from the `docs/` directory
* Run `jekyll serve` to locally host/inspect the docs.
